JOHANNESBURG - African National Congress (ANC) stalwarts are holding a three-day consultative conference at Constitution Hill in Johannesburg. They had wanted the party itself to convene the meeting, but it appears the leadership is against it. READ: ANC veterans hope to have conference soon The veterans wanted the conference to take place ahead of the ANC’s elective conference in December. The one theme that has been reverberating throughout the gathering is state capture. Members of civil society also expressed how dissatisfied they are, saying that the centre is simply not holding. Youth formations and the South African Communist Party (SACP) are also in attendance. eNCA